# Claude Code stores per-machine permission approvals here and auto-appends
# one-off command rules during sessions, which creates noisy churn. Ignore it by
# default. The canonical workflow permissions are documented in CLAUDE.md and are
# regenerated for any repo by scripts/Apply-GitWorkflow.ps1, so this file does not
# need to be tracked.
#
# This repo (the tooling source) can still capture a deliberate snapshot when you
# explicitly want one:
#     git add -f .claude/settings.local.json
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/settings.json

# Built binaries are distributed via GitHub Releases, not committed to the repo.
*.exe
